<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,223,826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">
The subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Wheeler" authorityYear="1986" box="[324,517,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Lymexylidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Melittommatinae">Melittommatinae</taxonomicName>
was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wheeler, Q. D." box="[726,904,223,250]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" pagination="113 - 210" refId="ref29469" refString="Wheeler, Q. D. (1986) Revision of the genera of Lymexylidae (Coleoptera: Cucujiformia). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 183, 113 - 210." type="journal article" year="1986">Wheeler (1986)</bibRefCitation>
for those members of the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fleming" authorityYear="1821" box="[1290,1436,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Lymexylidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lymexylidae</taxonomicName>
in which the elytra completely conceal the abdomen or expose at most two abdominal terga, and the larvae have a heavily sclerotised, truncate tergite IX. The largest genus in this group is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Murray" authorityYear="1867" box="[959,1094,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Lymexylidae" genus="Melittomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[959,1094,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">Melittomma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with about 20 species primarily in tropical and subtropical regions of both Western and Eastern Hemispheres. Other currently recognised genera include 
<taxonomicName authority="Lane (1955)" authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1955" box="[240,565,367,394]" class="Insecta" family="Lymexylidae" genus="Melittommopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[240,419,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">Melittommopsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lane, F." box="[426,565,367,394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" pagination="141 - 164" refId="ref28261" refString="Lane, F. (1955) Novos generos e especies de Coleoptera Lymexylonidae e notas sobre Melittomma Murray, 1867. Papeis Avulsos do Departamento de Zoologia, Sao Paulo, 12, 141 - 164." type="journal article" year="1955">Lane (1955)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, with at least four species from South America, the monotypic 
<taxonomicName authority="Wheeler (1986)" authorityName="Wheeler" authorityYear="1986" class="Insecta" family="Lymexylidae" genus="Protomelittomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">Protomelittomma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wheeler, Q. D." box="[192,369,403,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" pagination="113 - 210" refId="ref29469" refString="Wheeler, Q. D. (1986) Revision of the genera of Lymexylidae (Coleoptera: Cucujiformia). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 183, 113 - 210." type="journal article" year="1986">Wheeler (1986)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry box="[479,599,403,429]" name="Seychelles" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[654,789,403,429]" name="Madagascar" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and the Australian 
<taxonomicName authority="Wheeler (1986)" authorityName="Wheeler" authorityYear="1986" box="[1007,1382,403,430]" class="Insecta" family="Lymexylidae" genus="Australymexylon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1007,1195,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">Australymexylon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wheeler, Q. D." box="[1202,1382,403,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" pagination="113 - 210" refId="ref29469" refString="Wheeler, Q. D. (1986) Revision of the genera of Lymexylidae (Coleoptera: Cucujiformia). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 183, 113 - 210." type="journal article" year="1986">Wheeler (1986)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The remaining fossil species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirejtshuk (2008)" authorityName="Kirejtshuk" authorityYear="2008" box="[441,961,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Lymexylidae" genus="Ponomarenkylon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexandri">
<emphasis box="[441,747,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">Ponomarenkylon alexandri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk, A. G." box="[757,961,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" pagination="63 - 65" refId="ref28002" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. (2008) A new genus and species of timber beetle (Coleoptera: Lymexylidae) from Baltic amber. Paleontological Journal, 42 (1), 63 - 65." type="journal article" year="2008">Kirejtshuk (2008)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, an apparent Melittommatine from Baltic amber differ from other lymexylids in having: 1) very large eyes, (2) unusually short prothorax 3) filiform antennae and 4) the apparent connation of the first three abdominal ventrites (straight margins separating the first three ventrites and curved margins separating 3 from 4 and 4 from 5). Only a re-examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[1197,1295,547,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">holotype</typeStatus>
will support or refute the authorâ€™s hypothesis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,223,826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">
More than 20 years ago, the genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fairmaire (1895)" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1895" box="[621,941,619,646]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Alcestoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[621,738,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">Alcestoma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fairmaire, L." box="[747,941,619,646]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" pagination="336 - 398" refId="ref27372" refString="Fairmaire, L. (1895) Materiaux pour la faune coleopterique de la region Malgache. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 29, 336 - 398." type="journal article" year="1895">Fairmaire (1895)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fleming" authorityYear="1821" box="[1169,1315,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Lymexylidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lymexylidae</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Melandryidae</taxonomicName>
in a supplement to a paper dealing with a portion of the beetle fauna of the Prioksko-Terrasny Biosphere Reserve in the 
<collectingRegion box="[319,507,691,718]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">Moscow Region</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[519,594,691,717]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nikitsky, N. B. &amp; Semenov, V. B. &amp; Dolgin, M. M." box="[608,837,691,718]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" pagination="1 - 63" refId="ref28881" refString="Nikitsky, N. B., Semenov, V. B. &amp; Dolgin, M. M. (1998) The beetles of the Prioksko-Terrasny Biosphere Reserve Xylobionts, Mycetobionts, and Scarabaeidae (with a review of the Moscow Region fauna of these groups). Supplement 1 (with remarks on nomenclature and systematics of some Melandryidae of the world fauna) Sbornik Trudov Zoologicheskogo Muzeya M. G. U. (Archives of the Zoological Museum of Moscow State University), 36 (Supplement 1), 1 - 63. [in Russian with English summary]" type="journal article" year="1998">
Nikitsky 
<emphasis box="[714,763,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">et al</emphasis>
. 1998
</bibRefCitation>
). Fortunately, Dr. Nikitsky photographed the 
<typeStatus box="[1348,1407,692,718]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">types</typeStatus>
in his possession and sent me a habitus figure plus several detailed images. Based on these images, there is little doubt that this species is congeneric with 
<taxonomicName authority="Fairmaire (1893)" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1893" box="[543,971,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Lymexylidae" genus="Melittomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insulare">
<emphasis box="[543,775,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">Melittomma insulare</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fairmaire, L." box="[781,971,763,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" refId="ref27350" refString="Fairmaire, L. (1893) Communications. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France Bulletin, 62, cccxxii-cccxxv." type="book" year="1893">Fairmaire (1893)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1078,1201,763,789]" name="Seychelles" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
, which was made the 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,800,826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Wheeler (1986)" authorityName="Wheeler" authorityYear="1986" box="[325,705,799,826]" class="Insecta" family="Lymexylidae" genus="Protomelittomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[325,520,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="213">Protomelittomma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wheeler, Q. D." box="[526,705,799,826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="213" pagination="113 - 210" refId="ref29469" refString="Wheeler, Q. D. (1986) Revision of the genera of Lymexylidae (Coleoptera: Cucujiformia). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 183, 113 - 210." type="journal article" year="1986">Wheeler (1986)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
